President Cyril Ramaphosa gave his state of the nation (Sona) address in parliament on Thursday. Big names such as Springbok rugby captain Siya Kolisi, Miss Universe Zozibini Tunzi and Duduzane Zuma, son of former president Jacob Zuma, attended Sona 2020. Ministers and politicians have weighed in about the event, and TimesLIVE was there to hear what they had to say.